The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Anand beats Kamsky 
                                                   Anand beats Kamsky 
                      
	Nice: World Champion Viswanathan Anand survived some anxious moments in the blindfold game before registering a thumping victory in the rapid to register a clinical 1.5-0.5 victory over Gata Kamsky in the second round of the Amber blindfold and rapid chess tournament here.         
	Levon Aronians great start in the first round came to a halt as the Armenian dropped his queen and lost to Peter Leko in blindfold.         
	Aronian, however, struck back in the rapid game to steer the match to a draw and also made sure that he shared the top spot with Russian Alexander Morozevich who scored a 2-0 victory over Wang Yue.         
	With Aronian and Morozevich on three points in the combined standings, Anand and his world championship challenger Vladimir Kramnik of Russia are at joint third with 2.5 points each.         
